# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Credentials & secrets
#
# Jun 2026 policy update: real .env files are GITIGNORED. GitHub Push
# Protection blocked us when a live Stripe restricted key landed in
# backend/.env. Going forward, the source of truth for production
# secrets is the Emergent platform secret store (configured via the
# deployment UI / supervisor environment= blocks), and every developer
# uses a local-only `backend/.env` + `frontend/.env` that's never
# committed. `backend/.env.example` + `frontend/.env.example` document
# the required keys with placeholder values.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
credentials.json
*token.json*
*credentials.json*
*.pem
*.key
.credentials

# Apple ASC API Key + secrets
secrets/
*.p8
credentials*.disabled-*

# Allow EAS local credentials.json for iOS build pipeline
!frontend/credentials.json

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .env files — IGNORED. Use .env.example as the committed template.
# Production secrets are injected via the Emergent platform's secret
# store at runtime (see /etc/supervisor/conf.d/*.conf `environment=`
# blocks), NOT via committed dotenv files.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
*.env
!*.env.example
!.env.example
